# Backend Instructions

## Local rules
- follow the dominant backend patterns already present in adjacent files
- keep changes local before introducing new helpers, services, or abstractions
- protect public APIs, persistence semantics, migrations, and domain invariants
- prefer explicit failure handling and observable behavior
- treat unjustified new abstractions as a defect, not a neutral choice

## Verification
- run the smallest relevant backend checks first
- note the exact commands for build, lint, and targeted tests in `docs/agentic-workflow/ARCHITECTURE.md`
- if performance, concurrency, data integrity, or security are affected, say so explicitly
